value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 3 O2 + protoporphyrinogen IX = 3 H2O2 + protoporphyrin IX.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribose 5-phosphate + uracil = H2O + pseudouridine 5'-phosphate.

definition.value: Note that this term should not be confused with 'pseudouridine synthase activity ; GO:0009982', which refers to the intramolecular isomerization of uridine to pseudouridine.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: purine nucleoside + phosphate = purine + alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction:  pyridoxal + H2O + O2 = 4-pyridoxate + H+ + H2O2.

Catalysis of the reaction: pyridoxamine 5'-phosphate + H2O + O2 = pyridoxal 5'-phosphate + NH4+ + hydrogen peroxide. This activity can also oxidize pyridoxine 5'-phosphate to pyridoxal 5'-phosphate + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: a pyrimidodiazepine + oxidized glutathione = 6-pyruvoyltetrahydropterin + 2 glutathione.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-proline + NADP+ = 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + bicarbonate + pyruvate = ADP + 2 H+ + oxaloacetate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a 2-oxo acid = an aldehyde + CO2.
Catalysis of the oxidative decarboxylation of pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: pyruvate + lipoamide = S-acetyldihydrolipoamide + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + pyruvate dehydrogenase (acetyl-transferring) = ADP + pyruvate dehydrogenase (acetyl-transferring) phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: O-phospho-L-seryl-[pyruvate dehydrogenase E1 alpha subunit] + H2O = L-seryl-[pyruvate dehydrogenase E1 alpha subunit] + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-N6-dihydrolipoyl-L-lysyl-[protein] + acetyl-CoA = (R)-N6-(S8-acetyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysyl-[protein] + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: = ADP + H+ + phosphoenolpyruvate => ATP + pyruvate.

Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-retinol--[retinol-binding protein] + NAD+ = all-trans-retinal--[retinol-binding protein] + H+ + NADH. Recognizes the substrate both in free form and when bound to cellular-retinol-binding-protein (CRBP1), but has higher affinity for the bound form.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 6,7-dimethyl-8-(1-D-ribityl)lumazine + H+ = 5-amino-6-(D-ribitylamino)uracil + riboflavin.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-ribose = ADP + D-ribose 5-phosphate.

label.value: ribonucleoside-diphosphate reductase activity, thioredoxin disulfide as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 2'-deoxyribonucleoside diphosphate + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O = ribonucleoside diphosphate + thioredoxin. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.

definition.value: When thioredoxin is substituted for glutaredoxin in the reaction, annotate instead to 'ribonucleoside-diphosphate reductase, glutaredoxin disulfide as acceptor ; GO:0036175'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribose 5-phosphate + ATP = 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + AMP + 2 H+.

definition.value: Note that this term has a MetaCyc pathway reference as the pathway only has a single step.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribulose 5-phosphate = D-xylulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-ribose 5-phosphate = D-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the cleavage of N6-(L-1,3-dicarboxypropyl)-L-lysine to release an amino acid (lysine or glutamate), with the concomitant reduction of an electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-saccharopine + H2O + NAD+ = 2-oxoglutarate + L-lysine + H+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-saccharopine + H2O + NADP+ = L-allysine + L-glutamate + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O + hydrogen selenide = AMP + 3 H+ + phosphate + selenophosphorate.
Catalysis of the reactions: 7,8-dihydrobiopterin + NADP+ = sepiapterin + NADPH + H+ and (6R)-L-erythro-5,6,7,8-tetrahydrobiopterin + 2 NADP+ = 6-pyruvoyl-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropterin + 2 H+ + 2 NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + H+ + palmitoyl-CoA = 3-dehydrosphinganine + CO2 + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + pyruvate = 3-hydroxypyruvate + L-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction: shikimate + NADP+ = 3-dehydroshikimate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + shikimate = 3-phosphoshikimate + ADP + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosylmethioninamine + putrescine = 5'-methylthioadenosine + spermidine.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + sphingomyelin = ceramide + choline phosphate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H+ + O2 + octadecanoyl-CoA = (9Z)-octadecenoyl-CoA + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-oxo-delta(5)-steroid = a 3-oxo-delta(4)-steroid.
Catalysis of the reaction: a sterol ester + H2O = a fatty acid + a sterol + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA + a sterol = a sterol ester + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-beta-hydroxyandrost-5-en-17-one 3-sulfate + H2O = 3-beta-hydroxyandrost-5-en-17-one + sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: succinate + CoA + nucleotide triphosphate = nucleotide diphosphate + phosphate + succinyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + succinate + CoA = ADP + succinyl-CoA + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + succinate + CoA = GDP + succinyl-CoA + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: succinate semialdehyde + NAD+ + H2O = succinate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + succinyl-CoA = CoA + H+ + succinate.
Catalysis of the transfer of an adenylyl group from an adenosine nucleotide (ATP or ADP) to sulfate, forming adenylylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ADP + H+ + sulfate = 5'-adenylyl sulfate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + sulfate = diphosphate + adenylylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-sulfino-L-alanine = hypotaurine + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction: hydrogen sulfide + 3 NADP+ + 3 H2O = sulfite + 3 NADPH + 3 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 superoxide + 2 H+ = O2 + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: thiamine diphosphate + H2O = thiamine monophosphate + phosphate.
